article.description: Kenny Hayes had 22 points and Julian Mavunga added 13 points and 11 rebounds to lead Miami (Ohio) to a 74-69 victory at Northern Illinois.
article.headline: Northern Illinois rallies from 18 down, but then falls short to Miami (Ohio)
article.linkText: Northern Illinois falls short against Miami (Ohio)
article.story: DeKALB, Ill. -- Kenny Hayes had 22 points and Julian Mavunga added 13 points and 11 rebounds to lead Miami (Ohio) to a 74-69 victory at Northern Illinois on Saturday. Nick Winbush had 17 points and Antonio Ballard 12 for the RedHawks (10-13, 7-3 MAC). Darian Anderson had 16 points and Xavier Silas 13 for Northern Illinois (8-14, 4-6). Miami shot a season-high 63.2 percent (12 of 19) from 3-point range and held off the Huskies after they rallied to tie the game at 57-57 with seven minutes remaining. Northern Illinois trailed by 18 points at halftime.
